102 patients with mental disorders were examined using Adverse Childhood Experience Questionnaire (ACEQ), Russian-language validated Internalized Stigma of Mental Illness (ISMI) scale and Treatment Motivation Assessment Questionnaire (TMAQ).</p></sec><sec id="sec8053"><title>Results</title><p>
As a result of regression analysis (table 1), a model was obtained that predicted an increase in the chances of high patient&#x02019;s motivation for treatment with an increase in the total score of ACEs (ACEQ total score) and with higher education. The overall severity of internal stigma (ISMI total score) did not show a significant effect on the chances of developing intense motivation in patients.<table-wrap position="anchor" id="tab37"><label>
